title: Interdisciplinary (General Engineer/Operations Research Analyst)
description: The position(s) covered by this vacancy announcement is in the Department of Defense (DoD) Acquisition Workforce Personnel Demonstration Project (AcqDemo). For more information please see: AcqDemo

title: INTERDISCIPLINARY ENGINEER/COMPUTER SCIENTIST
description: You will serve as a Distinguished Scientist or Distinguished Engineer (D S/E) in the Software Engineering Department, Science and Technology Office of NAVAIRWARCENAC DIV. The Secretary of Defense has ordered a department-wide hiring freeze subject to certain limited exceptions. This position is subject to the DoD hiring freeze. Offers of employment related to this vacancy announcement will not be executed until the position has an approved exemption.

title: Financial Management Analyst
organization: Office of the Secretary of Defense
description: The Under Secretary of Defense (Comptroller/Chief Financial Officer (USD(C)/FCO) is responsible for carrying out the functions assigned by Section 135 of Title 10, United States Code, and assuring the utmost economy and efficiency in the operations of the Department of Defense (DoD). This position serves as senior analyst in support of Enterprise Financial Transformation (EFT) efforts to streamline and standardize financial operations and consolidate Financial Management (FM) systems.

title: Marine Interdiction Agent
description: This position is covered by Law Enforcement Availability Pay (LEAP). LEAP is an additional compensation of 25% of the base salary and locality pay. See additional pay information in the Duties section. Organizational Location: This position is with the Department of Homeland Security, within U.S. Customs and Border Protection, Air and Marine Operations.

title: Chief Artificial Intelligence Officer
description: The United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO) is seeking a Chief Artificial Intelligence Officer (CAIO) to advance the shared understanding of how to best implement the opportunities presented by Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML). The CAIO is the principal advisor to the Chief Information Officer (CIO) and the Deputy CIO on operationalizing AI and ML with a focus on business value delivery to the agency.

title: Chief Information Officer
description: The United States Patent & Trademark Office (USPTO) is headquartered in Alexandria, VA. The mission of the USPTO is to promote innovation and competitiveness by providing quality and timely examination and issuance of patent and trademark applications, guiding domestic and international intellectual property policy, and delivering intellectual property information and education worldwide.

title: Computer Engineer (Artificial Intelligence Engineer)
description: This is a term position. This position is located at Departmental Offices,Management CFO - Information Systems and Chief Information Officer. The incumbent is a senior computer engineer with specialized experience in the application of artificial intelligence (AI), computer engineering, data engineering, and emerging digital technologies to the Treasury's enterprise systems.
